cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY 

This paper investigates the evolution of the Internet topologies at the autonomous system (AS) level, which is closely related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves data analysis and modeling, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of IPv6-over-IPv4 tunnelling deployment scheme, which could be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
